{#-
  Search-CommandPalette — global ⌘K command palette wrapper (Ring 3 S3.3b-2).

  Pure composition Command Ring 2 with search-themed defaults + optional
  consumer-provided launcher button (typically in app header). NO new
  controller — Command Ring 2 already ships its own (dialog+combobox+command).

  The wrapper is value-add :
    - Provides the marker class `.theme-search-command-palette` for
      consumer styling differentiation.
    - Defaults placeholder + hotkey to search-focused values.
    - Documents the launcher button pattern (header button + ⌘K hint
      Kbd inline).

  Fuzzy search : NO. Command's substring filter (inherited from Combobox)
  suffices. Fuse.js stays manifest.thirdPartyLibs.fuzzy:FuseJS = candidate
  ring 2 — future Ring 4+ amend if typo-tolerant search needed (per
  OQ-NEW sealed at S3.3b-2 opening).

  Parameters (pass-through to Command Ring 2):
    htmlId       (string, optional)
    label        (string, optional, default 'Recherche globale')
    placeholder  (string, optional, default 'Rechercher projets, tâches, documents…')
    hotkey       (string, optional, default 'k')
    commands     (array,  required)  — see Command Ring 2 spec for shape
    kbdFooter    (array,  optional)  — Kbd hint cluster in footer

  Optional consumer-provided launcher button (rendered separately by the
  consumer in the app header) — example template :

      <button type="button"
              class="theme-button theme-search-command-palette__launcher"
              data-variant="ghost"
              onclick="window.themeCommand.open()">
        <svg class="theme-icon" data-size="sm" aria-hidden="true">
          <use href="#icon-search"/>
        </svg>
        <span>{{ 'Rechercher…'|trans }}</span>
        <kbd class="theme-kbd theme-search-command-palette__launcher-kbd">⌘K</kbd>
      </button>
-#}

{%- set htmlId      = htmlId      | default('theme-search-command-palette-' ~ random()) -%}
{%- set label       = label       | default('theme.search-command-palette.label'|trans) -%}
{%- set placeholder = placeholder | default('theme.search-command-palette.placeholder'|trans) -%}
{%- set hotkey      = hotkey      | default('k') -%}
{%- set commands    = commands    | default([]) -%}
{%- set kbdFooter   = kbdFooter   | default([
  { keys: ['↑', '↓'], label: 'theme.command.footer.navigate'|trans },
  { keys: ['⏎'],      label: 'theme.command.footer.execute'|trans },
  { keys: ['Esc'],    label: 'theme.command.footer.dismiss'|trans },
]) -%}

{# Defer to Command Ring 2 with search-themed defaults + marker class. #}
<div class="theme-search-command-palette">
  {% include '@theme/components/command/command.html.twig' with {
    htmlId:      htmlId,
    label:       label,
    placeholder: placeholder,
    hotkey:      hotkey,
    commands:    commands,
    kbdFooter:   kbdFooter,
  } only %}
</div>
